remarks: The relation ` T ` is a strict order on ` S ` (a corollary of ~ wemapso2 ).  (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 28-May-2015.)
statement:
cantnfs.s $e |- S = dom ( A CNF B ) $.
cantnfs.a $e |- ( ph -> A e. On ) $.
cantnfs.b $e |- ( ph -> B e. On ) $.
oemapval.t $e |- T = { <. x , y >. | E. z e. B ( ( x ` z ) e. ( y ` z ) /\ A. w e. B ( z e. w -> ( x ` w ) = ( y ` w ) ) ) } $.
oemapso $p |- ( ph -> T Or S ) $.
$d A w x y z $.
$d B w x y z $.
$d S x y z $.
$d ph x y z $.
